full_content.content: Common reasons your dryer no sound
The most common reasons your dryer has no sound are a defective electronic control board, defective power supply board or an inoperative user interface control.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over 22.2M dryers. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Common dryer repair parts you may need
Replacing one of these dryer parts may fix your problem.

If the sound and signal functions are not functioning on your dryer, a faulty electronic control board might be the culprit. This board is responsible for sending signals to the control panel to manage sound and signal features. When there's no sound coming from the dryer, it could indicate corrupted internal logic in the electronic control board or a broken internal relay. If your clothes dryer is silent, it's best to have a Sears Home Services Technician inspect your appliance and replace the electronic control board if necessary.
How to replace the electronic control board in an electric dryer

If the display isn't functioning on your dryer, a faulty power supply board might require replacement. This board is responsible for distributing electrical current from the dryer's power cord to various components, including the electronic control board. If the power supply board fails to deliver power to the electronic control board or the control panel, the dryer won't power up. If your dryer is entirely unresponsive, it's advisable to schedule a visit from a Sears Home Services Technician to inspect the appliance. The technician will replace the power supply board if it's found to be defective.

If the sound feature on your dryer's control panel isn't functioning, a malfunctioning user interface control could be the culprit. This control unit is responsible for transmitting signals to the control panel to initiate alarms and sound functions. If the user interface control is defective, it won't send the correct signal to activate sound on the control panel. If you're experiencing issues with the sound on your dryer, it's advisable to schedule repair service. A Sears Home Services Technician will then visit your home to diagnose and resolve the problem.

What to expect when you experience a dryer no sound issue
How do I fix a no sound problem

Addressing most issues with no sound typically entails replacing the electronic control board, power supply board, or user interface control. Nevertheless, since various factors could contribute to the problem, conducting a comprehensive diagnosis is crucial for resolving it. An accurate diagnosis is pivotal for determining the cost of the repair.
Sears Home Services provides solutions for a dryer that has no sound

If your dryer lacks sound, it could stem from various causes. To prevent unnecessary part replacements, we suggest having a Sears Home Services expert conduct diagnostic tests to pinpoint the underlying issue. Our technicians possess extensive experience in diagnosing a wide range of dryer malfunctions.
What to expect with a dryer no sound diagnosis

Understanding and diagnosing issues with modern appliances can be challenging without the right expertise and training. Attempting repairs without proper diagnostic methods may lead to replacing parts without certainty. Over the last decade, appliances have evolved significantly, with electronic components that are hard to assess. DIY fixes on newer models are growing more complex.

full_content.content: Why isn’t my dryer making any sound?
A faulty control panel, broken buzzer or failed control board can prevent the dryer from making any sounds.
Could a defective control panel keep the dryer from making any sound?
If the chime or buzzer is an integral component of the control panel, then an internal failure in the control panel can prevent the dryer from making any sound.
How can I fix my dryer if it’s not making any sound?
Check the control settings and turn on the buzzer or chime if you find the setting turned off. Replace any failed component that is preventing the dryer from making control sounds.
What should I do if my dryer continues to be silent after replacing the control panel?
A failure in the electronic control board can also prevent the dryer from making control sounds. You may need to replace a defective control board.

Find the most common Samsung clothes dryer error codes and their solutions. Get professional help from Sears Home Services.
A dryer drum is the main interior component of a clothes dryer where clothes are placed to be dried. It rotates during the drying cycle, allowing heated air to circulate through the clothes.

A dryer filter, commonly known as a lint filter, is a component of a clothes dryer that captures lint and other debris from clothes during the drying process, preventing them from clogging the dryer vent.
A dryer pedestal is a platform that elevates a dryer off the ground, making it easier to load and unload laundry while also providing additional storage space in some models.

A dryer rack is an accessory for clothes dryers that provides a stationary platform to dry items without tumbling, ideal for delicate or bulky items, or shoes that might be damaged by the usual drying cycle.
